document.title: These are taken from the AQA Biology specification document

5694A47AD8904D7C965A63619B616B40.description:
Use an appropriate number of significant figures
in calculation.

B06EAF5E1FEC41DFADEC066D91CFE1CF.description:
Use prefixes and powers of ten for orders of
magnitude (eg tera, giga, mega, kilo, centi, milli,
micro and nano).

D79AD452E03E4282A14433D6B897079F.description:
Use SI units (eg kg, g, mg; km, m, mm; kJ,
J) and IUPAC chemical nomenclature unless
inappropriate.

DDB33B3F4F5D465B8AFB2BD51F6659F5.description:
Recognise the importance of scientific quantities
and understand how they are determined.

9C368E1432F14525A9EB1F7B79FA5B80.description:
Use scientific vocabulary, terminology and
definitions.

95AEAA1B5BA6469FA82A89DD2EC296F4.description: WS4 Scientific vocabulary, quantities, units, symbols and nomenclature

453E3D4D64E74E689C8BD1E4DCDD1C03.description:
Communicating the scientific rationale for
investigations, methods used, findings and
reasoned conclusions through paper-based and
electronic reports and presentations using verbal,
diagrammatic, graphical, numerical and symbolic
forms.

8849A92CEA354CE7840AEA0F728F96A2.description:
Being objective, evaluating data in terms
of accuracy, precision, repeatability and
reproducibility and identifying potential sources
of random and systematic error.

79D3E95F2EAF4FCF92D8CA436F6A05A7.description:
Presenting reasoned explanations including
relating data to hypotheses.Â

4FACBDBF20424126A2470BD0061C2D52.description:
Interpreting observations and other data
(presented in verbal, diagrammatic, graphical,
symbolic or numerical form), including identifying
patterns and trends, making inferences and
drawing conclusions.

3EABDB828C0C440DB98239071F7121B1.description:
Representing distributions of results and make
estimations of uncertainty.

17E790AAE458470889E9FC31EC93FD67.description:
Carrying out and represent mathematical and
statistical analysis.

B2A1520332754D2FBC610647C5BC690B.description: Translating data from one form to another.

F594EAFD56A34E05A07EE989F58F492F.description:
Presenting observations and other data using
appropriate methods.

568A90615638492FA694E381C2E976ED.description:
Evaluate methods and suggest possible
improvements and further investigations.

253CCDC8ABA74B7B9E906466E8EEA932.description:
Make and record observations and
measurements using a range of apparatus and
methods.

928F0B92F65849BC911425EA69801A48.description:
Recognise when to apply a knowledge of
sampling techniques to ensure any samples
collected are representative.

E3314491D3FF49FEAC99B67C8B822188.description:
Carry out experiments appropriately having due
regard for the correct manipulation of apparatus,
the accuracy of measurements and health and
safety considerations.

3CE83A41FDD444D5B57FB7794F37286C.description:
Apply a knowledge of a range of techniques,
instruments, apparatus, and materials to select
those appropriate to the experiment.

5A025697C30748A78E5B596B8E8E30CE.description:
Plan experiments or devise procedures to
make observations, produce or characterise
a substance, test hypotheses, check data or
explore phenomena.

FA8045F52208493AB1DADD7B3E7F2C91.description:
Use scientific theories and explanations to
develop hypotheses.

8451ECA20A864C7AB5EC3C64D68961A6.description:
Recognise the importance of peer review of
results and of communicating results to a range
of audiences.

9F04017EC3AE4FCD92D8B940C99EB564.description:
Evaluate risks both in practical science and the
wider societal context, including perception of
risk in relation to data and consequences.

D99506E3C93A4D5791CEF672431CC482.description:
Explain everyday and technological applications
of science; evaluate associated personal, social,
economic and environmental implications; and
make decisions based on the evaluation of
evidence and arguments.

8905FAF26B5F451A9FED74F231CB2237.description:
Appreciate the power and limitations of science
and consider any ethical issues which may arise.

92383CF4985E4233B9CE85F7D0A71A8F.description:
Use a variety of models such as representational,
spatial, descriptive, computational and
mathematical to solve problems, make
predictions and to develop scientific explanations
and understanding of familiar and unfamiliar
facts.

3A2E7FF753E74313911B8324D9AF0D87.description:
Understand how scientific methods and theories
develop over time
